<worksheet xml:id="basics-sample-worksheet">
  <title>A Skeletal Worksheet</title>
  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>Something really cool</li>
      <li>A less important thing you'll learn</li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>
  <introduction>
    <p>It can be helpful to say what the point of the worksheet is.</p>
  </introduction>

  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>A first exercise, given one inch of blank workspace.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <sidebyside widths="45% 45%" valign="top">
      <exercise workspace="2in">
        <statement>
          <p>Only inside a worksheet may an exercise go in a sidebyside.</p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
      <exercise workspace="2in">
        <statement>
          <p>And so this is a second column.</p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
    </sidebyside>
  </page>

  <page>
    <p>A second page, begun with an explicit page break.</p>
  </page>

  <conclusion>
    <p>Put something here because you might run out of time.</p>
  </conclusion>
</worksheet>
